            Tags = """["purchase-orders","procurement","auto-po","automation","admin"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Auto-PO Suggestions & Settings\n\nAuto-PO watches your demand and proposes the purchase orders you need to cover it — so as a buyer you spend your time reviewing and approving rather than hunting for shortfalls. It lives on the Purchase Orders page across two tabs: **Suggestions** (where the proposals appear) and **Settings** (admin-only, where you set how it behaves).\n\n### How It Works\n\nEach night the system looks at what you're on the hook to supply — mostly the parts your open sales orders will consume, plus any stock that has dropped below its reorder point. It compares that against what's already coming in on open POs and what's on the shelf. Wherever you're going to come up short, it groups the shortfall by part and preferred vendor and raises an **Auto-PO suggestion**: which part, which vendor, how many to order, the date you need it by, and the sales orders that created the need.\n\nThis check runs on its own overnight. An admin can also kick off a fresh check on demand from the Suggestions tab (see the Auto-PO Suggestions walkthrough) instead of waiting for the next night.\n\n### Three Modes\n\nThe **Default Mode** setting controls how far the overnight check goes with the suggestions it raises:\n\n- **Suggest** — it only raises suggestions. Nothing is ordered on its own. As a buyer you review each suggestion on the Suggestions tab and decide whether to convert it to a PO or dismiss it. This is the most cautious mode and the usual starting point.\n- **Draft** — it goes one step further and builds **Draft** purchase orders from the suggestions, then stops. The Drafts wait on the Orders tab for a buyer to review, adjust, and submit. You get the time savings of pre-built POs while keeping a human gate before anything goes to a vendor.\n- **Automatic** — it creates the purchase orders with no manual gate. Use this only for trusted, well-tuned replenishment where the demand and the vendor terms are reliable.\n\n### Settings Fields (Admin)\n\nThe **Settings** tab is visible only to admins. It has:\n\n- **Enable Auto-PO** — the master switch. When off, the overnight check raises no suggestions or POs. Turn this on before any of the other settings take effect.\n- **Default Mode** — Suggest, Draft, or Automatic, as described above. Required.\n- **Buffer Days** — a lead-time cushion (0–365). The system pulls each need forward by this many days so a suggestion comes up early enough to order, ship, and receive before you actually need the part. Larger buffers order earlier and carry more stock; smaller buffers order later and run leaner. Required.\n- **Notify Chat** — when on, the team gets a chat message after each check so they see new suggestions (or POs) are waiting, without having to watch the tab.\n\nMake your changes and click **Save**. Save stays off until the form is valid and you've changed something.\n\n### Availability & Roles\n\nAuto-PO has to be turned on for your install — if it's off, the Suggestions and Settings tabs won't work. Viewing and acting on suggestions is open to **Admins, Managers, and Office Managers**; **changing the Settings and running a check on demand are for Admins only**.\n\n### Choosing a Mode\n\nMost shops start in **Suggest**, build trust in what it's flagging, then move the reliable categories up to **Draft** so POs are pre-staged for a quick review. Save **Automatic** for the parts where you'd rubber-stamp every suggestion anyway. You can change the mode any time — it only affects future overnight checks.","sections":[]}"""
        });

